OL,3,CTeen who suffers daily seizures
OL,4,C'scared' for safety after transport
OL,5,Ccuts
OL,7,FSarah said: "Sometimes I've had to
OL,8,Fsupport his head while he's had a
OL,9,Fseizure in the car. There's been times
OL,10,Fwhere he has been pushed against me
OL,11,Fand I've been pushed into the side of
OL,12,Fthe door. It's an unpredictable
OL,13,Fcondition."
OL,15,FJoshua, who is hoping to study Sport
OL,16,FScience as a specialist college, says
OL,17,Fhe would feel "really scared" and
OL,18,F"upset" because he "would not have a
OL,19,FPA to talk to or to look after me."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
