OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F393A1754597947
OL,3,CTeen who suffers daily seizures
OL,4,C'scared' for safety after transport
OL,5,Ccuts
OL,7,F"I don't think it's feasible that a
OL,8,Fdriver could be driving a vehicle,
OL,9,Fconcentrating on the road ahead of him
OL,10,Fand keeping a closing an eye on
OL,11,FJoshua," Sarah explains.
OL,13,F"If Joshua did have a seizure in the
OL,14,Fvehicle, the driver has to find a safe
OL,15,Fspace to pull over and support him. If
OL,16,Fhe had a PA, that support would be
OL,17,Finstantly available."
